estuary.model

Class Entity

  • java.lang.Object
    • estuary.model.Entity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Barrier, KelpPlant, MovingEntity, Oyster, OysterGabion, Rock, SeaWall, Shore

    public class Entity
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Entity is super class for all objects within the game. Every entity has a position along with getters and setters for their position. Every entity also has a hitbox to handle collisions. Every entity has an animation
    Author:
    Sean Rajkowski

      • Entity

        public Entity(Vector2 position,
              Rectangle hitbox,
              Animation animation)
        Constructor that creates a new entity with a position, hitbox and animation.
        Parameters:
        position - position is the top left corner of the entity's hitbox
        hitbox - A rectangle that makes up the area in which the entity can collide with another entity
        animation - The current animation that the view will use to display the entity
